// Pokemon Insurgence curated patches.
//
// Source-text fixes for known Insurgence bugs that cripple iOS play.
// Replaces the runtime postload override approach (see
// scripts/postload/pokemon_region_fix.rb) with a script-source rewrite
// that's authoritative and platform-portable.
//
// Format: JoiPlay-compatible. Keys without prefix do literal substring
// replace; keys prefixed with "[regex]" use std::regex_replace
// ECMAScript syntax.
{
  "rpgm": [
    // 1. Fix `getRegion` Ruby-1.8 idiom that crashes on Ruby 3.
    //
    // Original (Scripts/186-Deuks_Region.rb:16-31):
    //   def getRegion
    //     z = getCountryCode.to_i
    //     z=1 if (z==2)
    //     x = z.to_s.split('').map      # <- bare .map returns
    //                                   #    Enumerator on Ruby 3
    //     y = x[0]                      # <- Enumerator has no #[]
    //     m = y.to_i
    //     ...
    //   end
    //
    // Replacement: short-circuit to `return 2` (English), matching the
    // game's own commented-out fallback in 157-PokemonUtilities.rb:125
    // ("Use 'English' by default"). The full body wouldn't work on
    // iOS anyway: `getCountryCode` reads from the Windows registry
    // (MiniRegistry::HKEY_CURRENT_USER) which doesn't exist outside
    // Windows, so the original always returned 0 (Unknown) on iOS
    // even before the Ruby-3 .map regression. Hard-coding 2 matches
    // user-visible behaviour on a properly-configured Windows
    // English install, which is what the game's UI is laid out for.
    //
    // The lazy [\s\S]*? matches across newlines (std::regex's `.`
    // doesn't include newline). Crucially, the closing `end` must
    // be at column 0 (no leading whitespace) - that's what
    // distinguishes the outer `end` of a top-level `def` from the
    // inner `end` of any if/while/begin block in the method body.
    // `getRegion`'s body in 186-Deuks_Region.rb DOES contain
    // `if/elsif/end` so a `\n\s*end\b` pattern would lazily snap
    // to the inner end and leave the outer end dangling, producing
    // a SyntaxError that skips the whole script and leaves
    // `getRegion` undefined - which then surfaces as
    // `NoMethodError: undefined ... getRegion` from PokeBattle_Trainer.
    // The `\nend\b` anchor (no leading whitespace before `end`)
    // forces the regex past every indented inner end to the real
    // method terminator.
    {
      "key": "[regex]def getRegion\\b[\\s\\S]*?\\nend\\b",
      "value": "def getRegion\n  return 2\nend"
    }
  ]
}
